http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Kidwai-hospital-to-get-new-OT-complex/article14005476.ece

The State-run Kidwai Memorial Institute of Oncology will soon get a new operation theatre (OT) complex and a renovated Dharmashala for patient attendants.Minister of State for Medical Education Sharan Prakash Patil and Infosys Foundation chairperson Sudha Murthy laid the foundation stone for the facilities at the hospital campus here on Monday.The new OT complex, with five theatres, will augment the existing seven operation theatres and bring down the waiting period for patients.Kidwai director K.B. Lingegowda said that on an average two supra-major surgeries are conducted in each OT now.“Due to the increasing patient load, the waiting period for surgeries is around two weeks. We want to bring down the waiting period and the additional OTs will help us bring reduce it to four days,” he said.Mr. Patil said that the OT complex will be constructed at a cost of Rs. 6 crore and the Dharmashala renovation at a cost of Rs. 2 crore.Infosys Foundation had agreed to construct another Dharmashala for patient attendants and the land for the same would be provided within the campus premises, he said.It will also get a renovated Dharmashala for attendants of patients